2007-08-23  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

	* configure.ac, NEWS: Version 7.0.0.2.

	* Makefile.am, prepare_sources.sh.in: Fixed rules for separate
	directory build and already unpacked sources.

2007-08-22  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

	* Makefile.am: Uncreased library version (should have been done
	for 7.0.0.0).

	* m4/advanced_shell.m4, m4/downloader_prog.m4: New files and new
	checks: AC_PARAMETER_EXPANSION_STRING_REPLACE_CAPABLE_SHELL,
	AC_CHECK_DOWNLOADER_PROG.

	* Makefile.am, prepare_sources.sh.in: Use values from configure.

	* prepare_sources.sh.in: Don't depend on Bash specific features.

2007-06-06  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

	* configure.ac, NEWS: Version 7.0.0.1.

	* prepare_sources.sh: Use trailing EOL for sed "c" command to get
	byte equal sources on all platforms.

	* amrwb-dhf-declaration.patch: New patch to fix incorrect
	declaration of dhf.

2007-04-30  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

	* configure.ac, NEWS: Version 7.0.0.0.

	* AUTHORS, COPYING, prepare_sources.sh, amrwb.spec,
	amrwb-any-cflags.patch: Use upstream version 7.0.0.

	* configure.ac: Fail on critical checks.

	* amrwb.spec.in: New file.

	* configure.ac, Makefile.am: Use AC_SEARCH_LIBS instead of
	explicit -lm.

2007-04-29  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

	* Makefile.am: Removed "order only" make targets. Use
	-no-undefined required for Windows.

	* Makefile.am, amrwb.spec, TODO: Fixed parallel build using
	readme.txt as reference time stamp.

	* prepare_sources.sh: Use recommended sed syntax. Change
	readme.txt first in order. Delete corrupted files in case of
	error.

	* configure.ac: More build checks based on autoscan. Support
	Windows dll.

	* README, configure.ac, Makefile.am: Use upstream version 7.0.0.

2007-04-13  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

	* configure.ac: Version 6.0.0.1.

	* amrwb-intsizes.patch, prepare_sources.sh, Makefile.am: Apply new
	patch.

	* Makefile.am, amrwb.spec: Do not package 26204-600.doc.

	* configure.ac: Fail if needed binaries are missing.

2007-03-21  Stanislav Brabec  <utx@penguin.cz>

